{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"??","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"optional","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"consuming","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s2qqoiyxSgABn_AByKXKtKRi_zlF1TL_xmfp"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"defaultValue"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"attribute","text":"@autoclosure"},{"kind":"text","text":" () "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s2qqoiyxSgABn_AByKXKtKRi_zlF1TL_xmfp","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"rethrows"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s2qqoiyxSgABn_AByKXKtKRi_zlF1TL_xmfp","text":"T"},{"text":"? ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ~Copyable","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"optional","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An optional value."}]}]},{"name":"defaultValue","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A value to use as a default. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"defaultValue"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"optional"},{"text":" have the same type.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A nil-coalescing operation unwraps the left-hand side if it has a value, or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns the right-hand side as a default. The result of this operation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be the same type as its arguments."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This operator uses short-circuit evaluation: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"optional"},{"type":"text","text":" is checked first,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"code":"defaultValue","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is evaluated only if ","type":"text"},{"code":"optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":". For example:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let goodNumber = Int(\"100\") ?? Int(\"42\")","print(goodNumber)","\/\/ Prints \"Optional(100)\"","","let notSoGoodNumber = Int(\"invalid-input\") ?? Int(\"42\")","print(notSoGoodNumber)","\/\/ Prints \"Optional(42)\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"goodNumber","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is assigned a value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"100","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" because","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int(\"100\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" succeeds in returning a non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" result. When","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"notSoGoodNumber","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is initialized, ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int(\"invalid-input\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" fails and returns","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and so ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int(\"42\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is called to supply a default value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Because the result of this nil-coalescing operation is itself an optional","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value, you can chain default values by using ","type":"text"},{"code":"??","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" multiple times. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"first optional value that isn’t ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stops the chain and becomes the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"result of the whole expression. The next example tries to find the correct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text for a greeting in two separate dictionaries before falling back to a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"static default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let greeting = userPrefs[greetingKey] ??","    defaults[greetingKey] ?? \"Greetings!\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"userPrefs[greetingKey]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has a value, that value is assigned to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"greeting","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If not, any value in ","type":"text"},{"code":"defaults[greetingKey]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will succeed, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if not that, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"greeting"},{"text":" will be set to the non-optional default value,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Greetings!\""},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:s2qqoiyxSgABn_AByKXKtKRi_zlF","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iPadOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"Mac Catalyst","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.10"},{"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"9.0"},{"unavailable":false,"depreca